snippet.textDisplay:
I think this series brings a lot of interesting lessons to mind, but this episode made one especially clear: witch-hunts hurt honest people more than they hurt liars. A culture composed of constant holier-than-thou accusations, identity suspicions, and guilty-until-proven-innocent behavior, is dangerous, provoked violence, and is harmful to all.
I’m glad this series is for fun and entertainment, because when people think like this in the real world, there’s no cash prize waiting at the end. Everyone loses.
